All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Downloader
The Downloader class is responsible for retrieving web content, processing it, and extracting relevant data for indexing.
Gateway
The Gateway class serves as the central access point for handling distributed search requests, managing communication between clients and storage barrels.
GatewayInterface
The GatewayInterface defines a remote interface for communication between clients and the distributed search system.
GoogolClient
The GoogolClient class provides a command-line interface for users to interact with the distributed search engine system.
IndexStorageBarrel
IndexStorageBarrel implements a distributed inverted index storage system for a search engine.
IndexStorageBarrelInterface
The IndexStorageBarrelInterface defines a remote interface for managing an inverted index and link graph for a distributed search engine.
ReliableMulticast
Class for managing reliable multicast communication.
URLQueue
URLQueue implements a persistent queue system for URL management in a distributed search engine.
URLQueueInterface
Remote interface for managing a URL queue in a distributed search system.
